{"name":"Defence","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>The capacity to avoid being hit by an opponent is fundamental in a violent Cosmos.</p>\n<p>This skill permits characters to increase their Defence Value (DV) by one (1) point per ranking, making them difficult to hit and injure.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"21elJRtD5SbP13K1"}
{"name":"Thrown Weapons","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>Your ability to throw small weapons such as darts, throwing axes and rocks, as well as using slings and other small propelled weapons. Add the ranking in this skill to attack rolls of throwing weapons. Although the skill does not apply to item not designed for throwing it reduce penalties when throwing improvised weaponry. For instance, Sharsh decides to throw a chair at an opponent, which ordinarily induces a -3 penalty. As Sharsh has a ranking of two in Thrown weapons he can reduce the penalty to -1 as a consequence.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3fpZO7JbEKP63wUk"}
{"name":"Axes","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>An axe is a blade mounted on a shaft borne in one or two hands. Characters versed in this skill are able to effectively wield all manners of battle-axes, hatchets and other varieties of short- to medium-shafted axes.</p>\n<p>The ranking in this skill is added to any attack rolls using axes or similar weapons.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8zL2wNIwtaC58R0t"}
{"name":"Bows","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>A weapon made from a curved piece of wood, bone or similar material joined at the ends by a taut string; used to propel arrows. Your ability to fire and hit with all manners of missile weapons such as bows.</p>\n<p>Add your ranking in this skill to missile attack rolls.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Arkg3d4DkPfuuYaM"}
{"name":"Flexible Weapons","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill grants proficiency to use all segmented weapons consisting of two or more parts joined by a flexible link, such as flails, whips and so on. Add the ranking in this skill to any attack rolls for flexible weapons.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IZjfgsnDPCA0fF40"}
{"name":"Blunt Weapons","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill encompasses short shaft-mounted bludgeoning weaponry such as hammers, maces, mauls and clubs.</p>\n<p>The ranking in this skill is added to any attack rolls using blunt weapons.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IysuALbmkfX1HQEQ"}
{"name":"Blade Weapons","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>Weapons consisting of a blade with a handle used for thrusting and slicing. Swords, saifs and scimitars are examples of blade weapons. This skill allows a character to use all manners of swords.</p>\n<p>Add the ranking in this skill to any sword attack rolls.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MPguaZR5fYkVeUVj"}
{"name":"Unarmed","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>The art of unarmed close combat uses the body itself as a weapon. Brass knuckles and spike knuckles, however, still count as unarmed combat as they rely mainly on the body itself for impact. Characters trained in unarmed combat increase their brawling damage to D4 rather than the regular D3.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RRxsAKQ9jUzpsA8q"}
{"name":"Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill enables a character to dodge incoming attacks or impacts. See Combat Manoeuvres. The dodge skill can likewise be used in non-combat situations by characters trying to avoid collisions. Dodge is only applicable in close combat.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WXWTap7YDLvuztL8"}
{"name":"Shields","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>While using the defensive capabilities of a shield a combatant suffers -3 penalty to all combat manoeuvres. The shield skill allows a character to reduce this penalty. A character with a skill ranking of one would reduce the penalty to -2, a ranking of 2 would reduce the penalty to -1, et cetera. In addition to this, the shield skill enables a character to perform a block action with the shield and even using it for attacking opponents as a combat manoeuvre with the skill ranking is added to the rolls.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"X5LGQI7o1bWcsja5"}
{"name":"Small Blade Weapons","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>The most common tool and personal weapon are small blades such as daggers, knives, punching daggers and the like. This skill allows characters to fight with all types of small blades in close combat adding the skill ranking to attack rolls.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZqQBMk0tdBUmzdAd"}
{"name":"Polearms","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>Blunt, bladed and pointed weapons mounted on long shafts for extended range, including staffs, spears, glaives, halberds and such. Add the ranking in this skill to any polearm attack rolls.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"c1aYW6pPSpLC3rL5"}
{"name":"Dual-Wielding","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill allows a combatant to wield an additional weapon, shield or other item with less penalties than normally applicable. Fighting concurrently with two weapons or a weapon and shield adds a -3 modifier to the primary hand weapon and a -6 modifier to the off-hand weapon. Each ranking of dual-wielding reduces this modifier by one. This skill is also applicable to simultaneous non-combat actions. A character with a dual-wielding ranking of one (1) would reduce the penalties to -2/-5 and so forth. Note that ranks in this skill can never become positive modifiers, only negate penalties. This reduction of penalties also applies to creatures with more than two arms.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ewkcTGLdumAMsVzW"}
{"name":"Pick Axes","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"combatskill","data":{"description":"<p>Weapons with a pointed blade mounted perpendicular on a short shaft, often used against armoured opponents due to armour- piercing properties. Pick axes include the crowbill, kama and similar weapons. The skill ranking is added to attack rolls.</p>","ranks":0,"specialisation":""},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O2c7NviicXsWWvNx"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"u38BlTbCjV9F0ebJ"}
